    <note>Zhou(1) Dun [28705] He refers to Boqi [28695] as a yougern brother (di), which must mean younger cousin. The logical sequence of generational names, Fire to earth to wood would confirm this and probably make Dun's father, Pu [28706], a great grandson of Bangcai [28704]. Dun clearly earned the jinshi degree late in life. Raozhou FZ (1511), p. 205. WDY, 2, p. 626.至大末為國子生，登至正五年進士</note>
